#:proof{:extraction {:phases {:execute "```clojure\n{:goal\n \"Show that a nonempty closed set X ⊂ ℝⁿ has a closest point to any y₀ ∉ X.\"\n :terms\n [{:name \"closed set\"\n   :meaning \"X is closed in ℝⁿ\"\n   :needed-because \"closedness ensures the infimum of distances is attained\"}\n  {:name \"infDist\"\n   :meaning \"inf{‖x - y₀‖ : x ∈ X}\"\n   :needed-because \"the problem asks to show this infimum is attained\"}\n  {:name \"proper space\"\n   :meaning \"ℝⁿ is proper: closed bounded = compact\"\n   :needed-because \"properness makes the Mathlib theorem apply\"}]\n :strategy\n [{:id :mathlib-closest-point\n   :formal-dependency \"IsClosed.exists_infDist_eq_dist [ProperSpace]\"\n   :informal-dependency \"closest point theorem for proper metric spaces\"\n   :why-this-now \"Mathlib has this theorem directly\"\n   :lean-target \"∃ x₀ ∈ X, ∀ x ∈ X, dist y₀ x₀ ≤ dist y₀ x\"\n   :mathlib-status \"available\"\n   :critical-path true}]\n :stage-status\n {:stage1 :pending :stage2 :pending :stage3 :pending :stage4 :pending}}\n```", :integrate "(1) Heine-Borel: closed bounded = compact in ℝⁿ. (2) Continuous function on compact set attains its minimum. (3) These two facts combine to give the closest point theorem. Memorize the two-step pattern."}, :dependency-graph nil, :arse-questions nil, :classification :partial, :phase-count 2, :dep-graph-count 0, :arse-count 0}, :classification :proved, :reclassification-reason "Post-hoc: zero sorry with substantive declarations", :output "\n\n---\n\n## 1. TARGET SANITY CHECK\n\n- **mentions-problem-objects?** YES — X closed nonempty subset of ℝⁿ (EuclideanSpace), y₀ external point, distance minimization.\n- **avoids-assuming-conclusion?** YES — `∃ x₀ ∈ X, ∀ x ∈ X, dist y₀ x₀ ≤ dist y₀ x` is the conclusion, derived from `IsClosed X` and `X.Nonempty`.\n- **meaningful-without-prose?** YES — standalone metric space theorem about distance minimizers.\n- **notes:** Mathlib has this as `IsClosed.exists_infDist_eq_dist` for `ProperSpace`. `EuclideanSpace ℝ (Fin n)` is a `ProperSpace` in Mathlib. The formal target bridges Mathlib's infDist formulation (`infDist x s = dist x y`) to the problem's formulation (`dist y x₀ ≤ dist y x` for all x ∈ X) via the property that `infDist x s ≤ dist x z` for `z ∈ s`. This should be closeable with ~5 lines: apply Mathlib's theorem, then show the infDist characterization implies the ∀-quantified bound.\n\n## 2. PROOF-PLAN.EDN\n\n```clojure\n{:goal\n \"Show that a nonempty closed set X ⊂ ℝⁿ has a closest point to any y₀ ∉ X.\"\n :terms\n [{:name \"closed set\"\n   :meaning \"X is closed in ℝⁿ\"\n   :needed-because \"closedness ensures the infimum of distances is attained\"}\n  {:name \"infDist\"\n   :meaning \"inf{‖x - y₀‖ : x ∈ X}\"\n   :needed-because \"the problem asks to show this infimum is attained\"}\n  {:name \"proper space\"\n   :meaning \"ℝⁿ is proper: closed bounded = compact\"\n   :needed-because \"properness makes the Mathlib theorem apply\"}]\n :strategy\n [{:id :mathlib-closest-point\n   :formal-dependency \"IsClosed.exists_infDist_eq_dist [ProperSpace]\"\n   :informal-dependency \"closest point theorem for proper metric spaces\"\n   :why-this-now \"Mathlib has this theorem directly\"\n   :lean-target \"∃ x₀ ∈ X, ∀ x ∈ X, dist y₀ x₀ ≤ dist y₀ x\"\n   :mathlib-status \"available\"\n   :critical-path true}]\n :stage-status\n {:stage1 :pending :stage2 :pending :stage3 :pending :stage4 :pending}}\n```\n\n## 3. FORMAL-ALIGNMENT.EDN\n\n```clojure\n{:main-claim\n {:informal-claim \"For X ⊂ ℝⁿ nonempty and closed, ∃ x₀ ∈ X with ‖x₀-y₀‖ ≤ ‖x-y₀‖ for all x ∈ X.\"\n  :formal-name \"closest_point_exists\"\n  :formal-target \"theorem closest_point_exists {n : ℕ} {X : Set (EuclideanSpace ℝ (Fin n))} (hX : IsClosed X) (hne : X.Nonempty) (y₀ : EuclideanSpace ℝ (Fin n)) : ∃ x₀ ∈ X, ∀ x ∈ X, dist y₀ x₀ ≤ dist y₀ x\"\n  :sanity-check\n  {:mentions-problem-objects? true\n   :avoids-assuming-conclusion? true\n   :meaningful-without-prose? true\n   :notes \"Mathlib has IsClosed.exists_infDist_eq_dist for ProperSpace. ℝⁿ is ProperSpace. Bridge infDist = dist to ∀-quantified bound via infDist_le_dist.\"}}\n :alignments\n [{:formal-name \"closest_point_exists\"\n   :formal-statement \"∃ x₀ ∈ X, ∀ x ∈ X, dist y₀ x₀ ≤ dist y₀ x\"\n   :informal-clause \"Main claim: closest point exists\"\n   :role :main-theorem}\n  {:formal-name \"IsClosed.exists_infDist_eq_dist\"\n   :formal-statement \"∃ y ∈ s, infDist x s = dist x y\"\n   :informal-clause \"Mathlib's closest point theorem for proper spaces\"\n   :role :helper-lemma}]}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**t96J03 — FULLY FORMALIZED, ZERO SORRY.** Third fully-closed problem in the batch.\n\n**1. Why it's hard:** Students must recognize this as a compactness argument, not a direct construction. The infimum d = inf ‖x - y₀‖ exists but might not be attained — the key is that closed + bounded = compact in ℝⁿ (Heine-Borel), so the minimizing sequence lives in a compact set and has a convergent subsequence. The trap: trying to use completeness alone (closed ≠ compact in general metric spaces) or forgetting that ℝⁿ is special (finite-dimensional ⟹ proper).\n\n**2. The key insight:** Intersect X with a closed ball centered at y₀ to get a compact set, then minimize the continuous function x ↦ ‖x - y₀‖ on this compact set (extreme value theorem).\n\n**3. Complete proof:** Written in execute.md — Bolzano-Weierstrass on the minimizing sequence in the closed ball.\n\n**4. Lean formalization — ZERO SORRY:**\n```lean\nobtain ⟨x₀, hx₀_mem, hx₀_dist⟩ := hX.exists_infDist_eq_dist hne y₀\nexact ⟨x₀, hx₀_mem, fun x hx => hx₀_dist ▸ infDist_le_dist_of_mem hx⟩\n```\nTwo lines. `IsClosed.exists_infDist_eq_dist` gives the closest point, `infDist_le_dist_of_mem` gives the universal bound.\n\n**5. What connects:**\n- **Projection onto convex sets:** in Hilbert space, the closest point in a CLOSED CONVEX set exists and is unique. Without convexity, existence fails in infinite dimensions.\n- **Best approximation:** closest point in a subspace of L² = orthogonal projection. This is the foundation of least-squares and Fourier analysis.\n- **Variational methods:** the direct method of calculus of variations generalizes this: minimize a functional on a set where minimizing sequences have convergent subsequences.\n- **Exam-day field kit:** (1) Heine-Borel: closed bounded = compact in ℝⁿ. (2) Continuous function on compact set attains its minimum. (3) These two facts combine to give the closest point theorem. Memorize the two-step pattern.", :frame-workspace {:frame/lean-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/T96J03/Apm_v2_t96J03_1775003096930", :frame/id "apm-v2-t96J03-1775003096930", :workspace/owner-repo "futon6", :workspace/generated-at "2026-04-01T00:24:56.952898Z", :frame/shared-extension-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Local", :frame/module-root "ApmCanaries.Frames.T96J03.Apm_v2_t96J03_1775003096930", :proof/problem-id "t96J03", :workspace/schema "proof-frame-workspace.v1", :frame/workspace-root "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t96J03/apm-v2-t96J03-1775003096930", :artifacts {:proof-plan "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t96J03/apm-v2-t96J03-1775003096930/proof-plan.edn", :formal-alignment "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t96J03/apm-v2-t96J03-1775003096930/formal-alignment.edn", :changelog "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t96J03/apm-v2-t96J03-1775003096930/changelog.edn", :execute-notes "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t96J03/apm-v2-t96J03-1775003096930/execute.md", :workspace-readme "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t96J03/apm-v2-t96J03-1775003096930/README.md", :workspace-metadata "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t96J03/apm-v2-t96J03-1775003096930/workspace.json", :lean-main "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/T96J03/Apm_v2_t96J03_1775003096930/Main.lean", :lean-scratch "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/T96J03/Apm_v2_t96J03_1775003096930/Scratch.lean"}}, :artifacts ["/home/joe/co